{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_cb1f049ee5684d3e9a1dbbfb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tmuxp\n2\t\n3\tSession manager for tmux, which allows users to save and load tmux sessions through simple configuration files. Powered by [libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux).\n4\t\n5\t[![Python Package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/tmuxp.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/tmuxp/)\n6\t[![Docs](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/docs/badge.svg)](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/)\n7\t[![Build status](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/tests/badge.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/actions?query=workflow%3A%22tests%22)\n8\t[![Code Coverage](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp)\n9\t[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/tmux-python/tmuxp.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/LICENSE)\n10\t\n11\t**New to tmux?** [The Tao of tmux](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux)\n12\tis available on Leanpub and [Amazon Kindle](http://amzn.to/2gPfRhC).\n13\tRead and browse the book for free [on the\n14\tweb](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux/read).\n15\t\n16\t**Have some spare time?** Help us triage and code review and the tracker. See [issue\n17\t#290](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/discussions/290)!\n18\t\n19\t# Installation\n20\t\n21\tpip:\n22\t\n23\t```console\n24\t$ pip install --user tmuxp\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\tIf you're managing the project with [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/), add tmuxp as a dependency instead:\n28\t\n29\t```console\n30\t$ uv add tmuxp\n31\t```\n32\t\n33\tTo run tmuxp without installing it globally, similar to `pipx`, invoke it with\n34\t[uvx](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/):\n35\t\n36\t```console\n37\t$ uvx tmuxp\n38\t```\n39\t\n40\tHomebrew:\n41\t\n42\t```console\n43\t$ brew install tmuxp\n44\t```\n45\t\n46\tDebian / ubuntu:\n47\t\n48\t```console\n49\t$ sudo apt install tmuxp\n50\t```\n51\t\n52\tNix:\n53\t\n54\t```console\n55\t$ [[ -z $(which tmux) ]] && (nix-env -i tmux && nix-env -i tmuxp) || nix-env -i tmuxp\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\tFind the package for your distro on repology: <https://repology.org/project/tmuxp/versions>\n59\t\n60\tDevelopmental releases:\n61\t\n62\t- [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/):\n63\t\n64\t  ```console\n65\t  pip install --user --upgrade --pre tmuxp\n66\t  ```\n67\t\n68\t  Or request the pre-release from a uv project environment:\n69\t\n70\t  ```console\n71\t  uv add 'tmuxp>=1.10.0b1'\n72\t  ```\n73\t\n74\t\n75\t- [uvx](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/):\n76\t\n77\t  ```console\n78\t  uvx tmuxp\n79\t  ```\n80\t\n81\t- [pipx](https://pypa.github.io/pipx/docs/):\n82\t\n83\t  ```console\n84\t  pipx install --suffix=@next 'tmuxp' --pip-args '\\--pre' --force\n85\t  ```\n86\t\n87\t  Then use `tmuxp@next load [session]`.\n88\t\n89\t# Load a tmux session\n90\t\n91\tLoad tmux sessions via json and YAML,\n92\t[tmuxinator](https://github.com/aziz/tmuxinator) and\n93\t[teamocil](https://github.com/remiprev/teamocil) style.\n94\t\n95\t```yaml\n96\tsession_name: 4-pane-split\n97\twindows:\n98\t  - window_name: dev window\n99\t    layout: tiled\n100\t    shell_command_before:\n101\t      - cd ~/ # run as a first command in all panes\n102\t    panes:\n103\t      - shell_command: # pane no. 1\n104\t          - cd /var/log # run multiple commands in this pane\n105\t          - ls -al | grep \\.log\n106\t      - echo second pane # pane no. 2\n107\t      - echo third pane # pane no. 3\n108\t      - echo fourth pane # pane no. 4\n109\t```\n110\t\n111\tSave as _mysession.yaml_, and load:\n112\t\n113\t```console\n114\ttmuxp load ./mysession.yaml\n115\t```\n116\t\n117\tProjects with _.tmuxp.yaml_ or _.tmuxp.json_ load via directory:\n118\t\n119\t```console\n120\ttmuxp load path/to/my/project/\n121\t```\n122\t\n123\tLoad multiple at once (in bg, offer to attach last):\n124\t\n125\t```console\n126\ttmuxp load mysession ./another/project/\n127\t```\n128\t\n129\tName a session:\n130\t\n131\t```console\n132\ttmuxp load -s session_name ./mysession.yaml\n133\t```\n134\t\n135\t[simple](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#short-hand-inline-style) and\n136\t[very\n137\telaborate](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#super-advanced-dev-environment)\n138\tconfig examples\n139\t\n140\t# User-level configurations\n141\t\n142\ttmuxp checks for configs in user directories:\n143\t\n144\t- `$TMUXP_CONFIGDIR`, if set\n145\t- `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, usually _$HOME/.config/tmuxp/_\n146\t- `$HOME/.tmuxp/`\n147\t\n148\tLoad your tmuxp config from anywhere by using the filename, assuming\n149\t_\\~/.config/tmuxp/mysession.yaml_ (or _.json_):\n150\t\n151\t```console\n152\t$ tmuxp load mysession\n153\t```\n154\t\n155\tSee [author's tmuxp configs](https://github.com/tony/tmuxp-config) and\n156\tthe projects'\n157\t[tmuxp.yaml](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/.tmuxp.yaml).\n158\t\n159\t# Shell\n160\t\n161\t_New in 1.6.0_:\n162\t\n163\t`tmuxp shell` launches into a python console preloaded with the attached\n164\tserver, session, and window in\n165\t[libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux) objects.\n166\t\n167\t```console\n168\t$ tmuxp shell\n169\t\n170\t(Pdb) server\n171\t<libtmux.server.Server object at 0x7f7dc8e69d10>\n172\t(Pdb) server.sessions\n173\t[Session($1 your_project)]\n174\t(Pdb) session\n175\tSession($1 your_project)\n176\t(Pdb) session.name\n177\t'your_project'\n178\t(Pdb) window\n179\tWindow(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project))\n180\t(Pdb) window.name\n181\t'your_window'\n182\t(Pdb) window.panes\n183\t[Pane(%6 Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project)))\n184\t(Pdb) pane\n185\tPane(%6 Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project))\n186\t```\n187\t\n188\tSupports [PEP\n189\t553](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0553/) `breakpoint()`\n190\t(including `PYTHONBREAKPOINT`). Also supports direct commands via `-c`:\n191\t\n192\t```console\n193\t$ tmuxp shell -c 'print(window.name)'\n194\tmy_window\n195\t\n196\t$ tmuxp shell -c 'print(window.name.upper())'\n197\tMY_WINDOW\n198\t```\n199\t\n200\tRead more on [tmuxp shell](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/cli/shell/) in\n201\tthe CLI docs.\n202\t\n203\t# Pre-load hook\n204\t\n205\tRun custom startup scripts (such as installing project dependencies)\n206\tbefore loading tmux. See the\n207\t[before_script](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#bootstrap-project-before-launch)\n208\texample\n209\t\n210\t# Load in detached state\n211\t\n212\tYou can also load sessions in the background by passing `-d` flag\n213\t\n214\t# Screenshot\n215\t\n216\t<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/master/docs/_static/tmuxp-demo.gif\" class=\"align-center\" style=\"width:45.0%\" alt=\"image\" />\n217\t\n218\t# Freeze a tmux session\n219\t\n220\tSnapshot your tmux layout, pane paths, and window/session names.\n221\t\n222\t```console\n223\t$ tmuxp freeze session-name\n224\t```\n225\t\n226\tSee more about [freezing\n227\ttmux](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/cli/freeze/) sessions.\n228\t\n229\t# Convert a session file\n230\t\n231\tConvert a session file from yaml to json and vice versa.\n232\t\n233\t```console\n234\t$ tmuxp convert filename\n235\t```\n236\t\n237\tThis will prompt you for confirmation and shows you the new file that is\n238\tgoing to be written.\n239\t\n240\tYou can auto confirm the prompt. In this case no preview will be shown.\n241\t\n242\t```console\n243\t$ tmuxp convert -y filename\n244\t$ tmuxp convert --yes filename\n245\t```\n246\t\n247\t# Plugin System\n248\t\n249\ttmuxp has a plugin system to allow for custom behavior. See more about\n250\tthe [Plugin System](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/topics/plugins/).\n251\t\n252\t# Debugging Helpers\n253\t\n254\tThe `load` command provides a way to log output to a log file for\n255\tdebugging purposes.\n256\t\n257\t```console\n258\t$ tmuxp load --log-file <log-file-name> .\n259\t```\n260\t\n261\tCollect system info to submit with a Github issue:\n262\t\n263\t```console\n264\t$ tmuxp debug-info\n265\t------------------\n266\tenvironment:\n267\t    system: Linux\n268\t    arch: x86_64\n269\t\n270\t# ... so on\n271\t```\n272\t\n273\t# Docs / Reading material\n274\t\n275\tSee the [Quickstart](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/quickstart/).\n276\t\n277\t[Documentation](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com) homepage (also in\n278\t[中文](http://tmuxp-zh.rtfd.org/))\n279\t\n280\tWant to learn more about tmux itself? [Read The Tao of Tmux\n281\tonline](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/about_tmux/).\n282\t\n283\t# Donations\n284\t\n285\tYour donations fund development of new features, testing and support.\n286\tYour money will go directly to maintenance and development of the\n287\tproject. If you are an individual, feel free to give whatever feels\n288\tright for the value you get out of the project.\n289\t\n290\tSee donation options at <https://tony.sh/support.html>.\n291\t\n292\t# Project details\n293\t\n294\t- tmux support: 3.2+\n295\t- python support: >= 3.10, pypy, pypy3\n296\t- Source: <https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp>\n297\t- Docs: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com>\n298\t- API: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/internals/api/>\n299\t- Changelog: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/history/>\n300\t- Issues: <https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/issues>\n301\t- Test Coverage: <https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp>\n302\t- pypi: <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/tmuxp>\n303\t- Open Hub: <https://www.openhub.net/p/tmuxp-python>\n304\t- Repology: <https://repology.org/project/tmuxp/versions>\n305\t- License: [MIT](http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).\n306\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90b69ae6-23a1-43ad-baa2-7ae0a0f9a4e0","uuid":"438bbdde-5b46-4987-8a6c-fb30dc615512","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:01:10.450Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"# tmuxp\n\nSession manager for tmux, which allows users to save and load tmux sessions through simple configuration files. Powered by [libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux).\n\n[![Python Package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/tmuxp.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/tmuxp/)\n[![Docs](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/docs/badge.svg)](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/)\n[![Build status](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/tests/badge.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/actions?query=workflow%3A%22tests%22)\n[![Code Coverage](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/tmux-python/tmuxp.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/LICENSE)\n\n**New to tmux?** [The Tao of tmux](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux)\nis available on Leanpub and [Amazon Kindle](http://amzn.to/2gPfRhC).\nRead and browse the book for free [on the\nweb](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux/read).\n\n**Have some spare time?** Help us triage and code review and the tracker. See [issue\n#290](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/discussions/290)!\n\n# Installation\n\npip:\n\n```console\n$ pip install --user tmuxp\n```\n\nIf you're managing the project with [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/), add tmuxp as a dependency instead:\n\n```console\n$ uv add tmuxp\n```\n\nTo run tmuxp without installing it globally, similar to `pipx`, invoke it with\n[uvx](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/):\n\n```console\n$ uvx tmuxp\n```\n\nHomebrew:\n\n```console\n$ brew install tmuxp\n```\n\nDebian / ubuntu:\n\n```console\n$ sudo apt install tmuxp\n```\n\nNix:\n\n```console\n$ [[ -z $(which tmux) ]] && (nix-env -i tmux && nix-env -i tmuxp) || nix-env -i tmuxp\n```\n\nFind the package for your distro on repology: <https://repology.org/project/tmuxp/versions>\n\nDevelopmental releases:\n\n- [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/):\n\n  ```console\n  pip install --user --upgrade --pre tmuxp\n  ```\n\n  Or request the pre-release from a uv project environment:\n\n  ```console\n  uv add 'tmuxp>=1.10.0b1'\n  ```\n\n\n- [uvx](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/):\n\n  ```console\n  uvx tmuxp\n  ```\n\n- [pipx](https://pypa.github.io/pipx/docs/):\n\n  ```console\n  pipx install --suffix=@next 'tmuxp' --pip-args '\\--pre' --force\n  ```\n\n  Then use `tmuxp@next load [session]`.\n\n# Load a tmux session\n\nLoad tmux sessions via json and YAML,\n[tmuxinator](https://github.com/aziz/tmuxinator) and\n[teamocil](https://github.com/remiprev/teamocil) style.\n\n```yaml\nsession_name: 4-pane-split\nwindows:\n  - window_name: dev window\n    layout: tiled\n    shell_command_before:\n      - cd ~/ # run as a first command in all panes\n    panes:\n      - shell_command: # pane no. 1\n          - cd /var/log # run multiple commands in this pane\n          - ls -al | grep \\.log\n      - echo second pane # pane no. 2\n      - echo third pane # pane no. 3\n      - echo fourth pane # pane no. 4\n```\n\nSave as _mysession.yaml_, and load:\n\n```console\ntmuxp load ./mysession.yaml\n```\n\nProjects with _.tmuxp.yaml_ or _.tmuxp.json_ load via directory:\n\n```console\ntmuxp load path/to/my/project/\n```\n\nLoad multiple at once (in bg, offer to attach last):\n\n```console\ntmuxp load mysession ./another/project/\n```\n\nName a session:\n\n```console\ntmuxp load -s session_name ./mysession.yaml\n```\n\n[simple](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#short-hand-inline-style) and\n[very\nelaborate](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#super-advanced-dev-environment)\nconfig examples\n\n# User-level configurations\n\ntmuxp checks for configs in user directories:\n\n- `$TMUXP_CONFIGDIR`, if set\n- `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, usually _$HOME/.config/tmuxp/_\n- `$HOME/.tmuxp/`\n\nLoad your tmuxp config from anywhere by using the filename, assuming\n_\\~/.config/tmuxp/mysession.yaml_ (or _.json_):\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp load mysession\n```\n\nSee [author's tmuxp configs](https://github.com/tony/tmuxp-config) and\nthe projects'\n[tmuxp.yaml](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/.tmuxp.yaml).\n\n# Shell\n\n_New in 1.6.0_:\n\n`tmuxp shell` launches into a python console preloaded with the attached\nserver, session, and window in\n[libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux) objects.\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp shell\n\n(Pdb) server\n<libtmux.server.Server object at 0x7f7dc8e69d10>\n(Pdb) server.sessions\n[Session($1 your_project)]\n(Pdb) session\nSession($1 your_project)\n(Pdb) session.name\n'your_project'\n(Pdb) window\nWindow(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project))\n(Pdb) window.name\n'your_window'\n(Pdb) window.panes\n[Pane(%6 Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project)))\n(Pdb) pane\nPane(%6 Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project))\n```\n\nSupports [PEP\n553](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0553/) `breakpoint()`\n(including `PYTHONBREAKPOINT`). Also supports direct commands via `-c`:\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp shell -c 'print(window.name)'\nmy_window\n\n$ tmuxp shell -c 'print(window.name.upper())'\nMY_WINDOW\n```\n\nRead more on [tmuxp shell](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/cli/shell/) in\nthe CLI docs.\n\n# Pre-load hook\n\nRun custom startup scripts (such as installing project dependencies)\nbefore loading tmux. See the\n[before_script](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#bootstrap-project-before-launch)\nexample\n\n# Load in detached state\n\nYou can also load sessions in the background by passing `-d` flag\n\n# Screenshot\n\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/master/docs/_static/tmuxp-demo.gif\" class=\"align-center\" style=\"width:45.0%\" alt=\"image\" />\n\n# Freeze a tmux session\n\nSnapshot your tmux layout, pane paths, and window/session names.\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp freeze session-name\n```\n\nSee more about [freezing\ntmux](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/cli/freeze/) sessions.\n\n# Convert a session file\n\nConvert a session file from yaml to json and vice versa.\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp convert filename\n```\n\nThis will prompt you for confirmation and shows you the new file that is\ngoing to be written.\n\nYou can auto confirm the prompt. In this case no preview will be shown.\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp convert -y filename\n$ tmuxp convert --yes filename\n```\n\n# Plugin System\n\ntmuxp has a plugin system to allow for custom behavior. See more about\nthe [Plugin System](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/topics/plugins/).\n\n# Debugging Helpers\n\nThe `load` command provides a way to log output to a log file for\ndebugging purposes.\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp load --log-file <log-file-name> .\n```\n\nCollect system info to submit with a Github issue:\n\n```console\n$ tmuxp debug-info\n------------------\nenvironment:\n    system: Linux\n    arch: x86_64\n\n# ... so on\n```\n\n# Docs / Reading material\n\nSee the [Quickstart](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/quickstart/).\n\n[Documentation](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com) homepage (also in\n[中文](http://tmuxp-zh.rtfd.org/))\n\nWant to learn more about tmux itself? [Read The Tao of Tmux\nonline](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/about_tmux/).\n\n# Donations\n\nYour donations fund development of new features, testing and support.\nYour money will go directly to maintenance and development of the\nproject. If you are an individual, feel free to give whatever feels\nright for the value you get out of the project.\n\nSee donation options at <https://tony.sh/support.html>.\n\n# Project details\n\n- tmux support: 3.2+\n- python support: >= 3.10, pypy, pypy3\n- Source: <https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp>\n- Docs: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com>\n- API: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/internals/api/>\n- Changelog: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/history/>\n- Issues: <https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/issues>\n- Test Coverage: <https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp>\n- pypi: <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/tmuxp>\n- Open Hub: <https://www.openhub.net/p/tmuxp-python>\n- Repology: <https://repology.org/project/tmuxp/versions>\n- License: [MIT](http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).\n","numLines":306,"startLine":1,"totalLines":306}}}
